The paper deals with the problem of constraint satisfaction, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The paper focuses on the structural tractability of the problem of enumerating solutions, which is a computational problem related to constraint satisfaction. The paper proposes a framework based on the notion of tree projection of hypergraphs, which is a well-known technique in computer science. The paper also presents tractability results for different classes of structures, which is a common approach in computer science research.
